    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - TURBOCHARGERS - RECONDITIONING</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl4150202">
        <title>RECONDITIONING</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
            <title>DISASSEMBLY</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Follow the turbo reconditioning procedures when the turbocharger fails one or more
                        pre-disassembly inspections.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the turbocharger removed from the engine as described in this section, cap all
                    openings.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wash the exterior of the turbocharger using Bendix Metal Cleaner or Gunk Hydroseal
                    Cleaner.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>
                            <emph type="underscr">DO NOT</emph>
                            use a caustic solution. Certain turbocharger parts may be damaged by exposure to a caustic
                            cleaner.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the turbocharger on a clean bench.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To make reassembly easier, mark the turbo-charger components as follows: (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150225">2.25</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    )
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Compressor housing-to-back plate.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Back plate-to-center housing.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Center housing-to-turbine housing.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the compressor housing capscrews and clamps at the back plate. Carefully lift the
                    turbine and center housing assembly from the compressor housing. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150226">2.26</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>CARE MUST BE TAKEN DURING THE HANDLING OF THE IMPELLER AND TURBINE WHEEL. BE VERY CAREFUL
                            AND AVOID BENDING ANY BLADES. BENT BLADES MUST NEVER BE USED.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the turbine housing capscrews and clamps which secure the center housing and core
                    assembly to the turbine housing. Carefully lift the center housing and core assembly from the
                    turbine housing. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150227">2.27</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150225" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11413" filename="../figcg1/cg11413.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.25 Mark Adjacent Components to Facilitate Reassembly.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150226" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11414" filename="../figcg1/cg11414.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.26 Removing Compressor Housing.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150227" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11415" filename="../figcg1/cg11415.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.27 Removing Turbine Housing from Center Housing.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
